# scripts/secrets/.secrets.example
#
# This file is a CHECKLIST for operators, NOT a config file.
# It lists the GitHub Actions Secrets that fetch_secrets.sh reads.
# The actual values live ONLY in the GitHub repo's Settings → Secrets
# and variables → Actions page; nothing here is sourced or parsed.
#
# To add a new secret:
#   1. Open the repo on GitHub → Settings → Secrets and variables → Actions
#   2. Click "New repository secret"
#   3. Name = one of the keys below (UPPER_SNAKE_CASE, exact spelling)
#   4. Value = the secret value
#   5. (For TENCENT_DB_ADMIN_URL) put it in Environment "production" with
#      required reviewers — it is a superuser DSN, blast radius is high
#   6. Verify with:
#        gh workflow run sync-secrets.yml -f which=all -f request_id=verify
#        # (then gh run download to confirm round-trip)

# ---- CMS segment (fetch_secrets.sh eval-cms) ----
#
# AI_API_KEY              sk-...                    # OpenAI-compatible
# AI_BASE_URL             https://api.openai.com/v1 # default in cms/.env.example
# AI_MODEL                gpt-3.5-turbo             # or gpt-4o / MiniMax-M3 / etc.
#
# TENCENT_SECRET_ID       AKID...                   # Tencent Cloud TTS
# TENCENT_SECRET_KEY      ...
# TENCENT_APP_ID          ...
#
# CLOUD_PROVIDER          tencent_cos               # or "local_fs" for no-cloud
# CLOUD_BUCKET            english-audio-xxx
# CLOUD_REGION            ap-guangzhou
# CLOUD_ACCESS_KEY        ...
# CLOUD_SECRET_KEY        ...
# CLOUD_ENDPOINT          (optional CDN custom domain)

# ---- DB segment (fetch_secrets.sh eval-db) ----
#
# TENCENT_DB_HOST         tencent-pg-xxx.tencentcloud.com:5432
# TENCENT_DB_USER         english_dev_alice         # or leave unset; derived from $USER
# TENCENT_DB_PASSWORD     24-char URL-safe          # matches the role password on db
# TENCENT_DB_PROD_USER    english_prod_user         # fixed; prod host only
# TENCENT_DB_PROD_PASSWORD 24-char URL-safe
# TENCENT_DB_ADMIN_URL    (一次性,只在 GH UI 配一次,见下)
#                        # 组成字段(分别存储,不要拼成完整 DSN 写进任何 git 跟踪文件):
#                        #   user = postgres
#                        #   password = <一次性 admin 密码,从腾讯云控制台获取>
#                        #   host = <TENCENT_DB_HOST 同值>
#                        #   port = 5432
#                        #   db   = postgres
#                        # 用途: bootstrap_tencent.sh 用它做 CREATE ROLE / DATABASE /
#                        #       GRANT(每个 host 一次),之后 reset-db / cleanup 不再需要。
#                        # ⚠️ 永远不要把完整 DSN 写进任何 git 跟踪文件 — 走 GH Secrets。

# Recommended workflow (GH Secrets path — no .secrets/tencent_db_admin_url file
# ever written to disk):
#
#   # 1. Push the 17 secrets once to GH (值的形态见上面 # ---- 段):
#   gh secret set AI_API_KEY --body "sk-..."
#   # TENCENT_DB_ADMIN_URL → GH Environment "production" + required reviewers
#   #   (UI 操作,gh CLI 写不到 environment secret; Settings → Environments)
#
#   # 2. On every host, every shell session:
#   cd <repo>
#   eval "$(scripts/secrets/fetch_secrets.sh eval-db)"   # or eval-all for cms too
#   ./ops/dev/setup.sh bootstrap                          # no file write needed
#   ./ops/dev/setup.sh reset-db                           # in-memory admin URL
#   ./ops/dev/setup.sh cleanup                            # in-memory admin URL

# Standalone fallback (no GH):
#   If you don't want to use GitHub Secrets at all (e.g. on an isolated
#   network), keep using cms/.env and .secrets/ as before. fetch_secrets.sh
#   is purely additive — its absence doesn't break anything.
